text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia dissona is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The shrub typically grows to a height of 0.5 to 2 metres (2 to 7 ft). It blooms from July to October and produces yellow flowers.
There are two recognised varieties:

Acacia dissona var. dissona
Acacia dissona var. indoloria
